      "Pressure bleed-down procedure initiated",
      "All clear given after approximately 1.5 hours"
    ],
    "summary": "On 13 July 2022 at 2045 hours, an overspeed trip caused Compressor #1 to shut down, creating backpressure that fed into the low pressure side of out-of-service Compressor #2. Gas escaped through an improperly installed blind flange (missing gasket) on Compressor #2. A nearby gas detector sensed the release and automatically shut in production and sounded a muster alarm. All 31 personnel on board safely mustered. No damage or pollution occurred.",
